@startuml
title ETR Study API — C4 Level 1 · System context
$Subtitle("Who calls the system, what it owns, what orbits it")

' Compact, balanced layout. The system box sits in the middle; the
' integrator is on top, the datastore below, and the two optional
' stacks (observability, log search) flank either side.
top to bottom direction

skinparam nodesep 40
skinparam ranksep 34

actor "Integrator\n//(HTTP client)//" as Integrator

rectangle "**ETR Study API**\nFastAPI · OpenAPI · /api/v1\n//Versioned · idempotent · rate-limited//" as Api

database "**Relational store**\nSQLite (dev) · PostgreSQL-capable\n//Owns schema & migrations//" as Db

package "Observability\n//(optional)//" as Obs {
  [Grafana]    as Graf
  [Prometheus] as Prom
  [Blackbox]   as Bbx
}

package "Log search\n//(optional)//" as LogSearch {
  [Elasticsearch] as ES
  [Kibana]        as Kib
}

' Primary runtime path — kept first so it lays out as the spine.
Integrator --> Api : HTTPS · JSON
Api        --> Db  : SQL · transactions

' Side stacks attach to the API from the flanks.
Prom -.> Api : scrape\n/metrics
Bbx  -.> Api : probe\n/ready
Graf --> Prom

Api -.> ES : NDJSON logs
Kib --> ES

note right of Integrator
  Any OpenAPI-compliant HTTP client —
  web, mobile, bots are downstream of this boundary.
end note

note bottom of Db
  Single-writer · transactional ·
  append-only review log and event journal.
end note

$LegendStandard()
$Footer("Conventions: ADR-0020 · regenerate with `make docs-fix`")
@enduml
